Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.
Boil the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g}, ~{12%minutes}.
Once cooked, drain and drizzle with @oil{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the @Diced British Chicken Thigh{240%g}, @Dried Oregano{1%sachet} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g}, ~{8-10%minutes}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g}, @Wild Mushroom Paste{15%g} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml} (see pantry).
Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Stir in the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} and cooked rigatoni until combined.

Share your pasta between your bowls.
Enjoy!